1. The data will be split into two groups, training set (train.csv) and test set (test.csv)
  - The training set should be used ot build machine learning models, and will be provided supervised data such that there exist ground truth data based on the features given
  - The test set shold be used to see how the model performs on unseen data, the test set does not provide the ground truth data as it is up to the model to predict on this data
Data Dictionary:
Survivial - a boolean representing whether a person survived or not denoted by 0=no and 1 = Yes
pclass - The ticket class 1=1st class, 2 = 2nd class, and 3 = 3rd class
sex - is either male or female in this data set
age - the age of the person given in years
sibsp -  the number of sibilings and spouses aboard the titanic given as an integer
parch - the number of parents and childern aboard the titanic given as an integer
ticket - the ticket number given as an integer
fare - the passenger fare in dollars given as  (float, or int?)
cabin -  the cabin number given as an integer
embarked - the port of embarkment given as a single letter to denote the port, C = Cherbourg, Q = Queenstown, and S = Southhampton

Varible notes from Kaggle
pclass: A proxy for socio-economic status (SES)
1st = Upper
2nd = Middle
3rd = Lower

age: Age is fractional if less than 1. If the age is estimated, is it in the form of xx.5

sibsp: The dataset defines family relations in this way...
Sibling = brother, sister, stepbrother, stepsister
Spouse = husband, wife (mistresses and fiancés were ignored)

parch: The dataset defines family relations in this way...
Parent = mother, father
Child = daughter, son, stepdaughter, stepson
Some children travelled only with a nanny, therefore parch=0 for them.

